column1: OMAP-11 Organ Mapping Antibody Panel (OMAP) for Multiplexed Antibody-Based Imaging of Human Spleen with IBEX

column2: Danny Jonigk; Ronald N. Germain; Ellen Quardokus; Diane Saunders

column24: rationale

Defines follicular dendritic cell meshworks in primary follicles, secondary follicles, and germinal centers. This marker is essential for defining follicular dendritic cells and represents a prioritized target in the spleen OMAP.
Defines stromal cells of the red pulp as well as follicular dendritic cells in the follicles.
Defines B cell follicles and is an essential marker of B cells. This marker represents a core marker and prioritized target in the spleen OMAP.

Defines red pulp based on enrichment of CD68+ macrophages in this anatomical structure. This marker is expressed by many subsets of myeloid cells (tingible body macrophages, proinflammatory M1 macrophages, dendritic cells). This marker represents a core marker and prioritized target in the spleen OMAP.
This marker cannot be used to define a specific anatomical structure but is expressed by red blood cells in the red pulp.

This marker cannot be used to define a specific anatomical structure and exists as a soluble protein in the plasma. It is detected using an anti-sheep secondary antibody (Thermo Fisher Scientific A-21102) and is not a prioritized target for the spleen OMAP.
Secondary antibody used to detect Fibrinogen, see above.
Defines red pulp based on enrichment of CD163+ macrophages in this anatomical structure. This marker represents a prioritized target in the spleen OMAP.
Defines red pulp based on labeling of splenic stromal cells including reticular cells of the sinusoids. This marker represents a core marker and prioritized target in the spleen OMAP.
This marker cannot define an anatomical structure alone but identifies plasma cells/plasmablasts. This marker represents a prioritized target in the spleen OMAP.
This marker is expressed by monocytes and neutrophils. This marker represents a prioritized target in the spleen OMAP.
Secondary antibody used to detect CD15, see above.
This marker is expressed by professional antigen presenting cells including B cells (HLA-DR+) and dendritic cells (HLA-DR++). This marker represents a prioritized target in the spleen OMAP.
This antibody cannot be used to define a specific anatomical structure but targets an essential marker for dendritic cells. This marker represents a prioritized target in the spleen OMAP.
Defines stromal network of spleen and serves as a pan-mesenchymal cell marker. This marker represents a prioritized target in the spleen OMAP.

This antibody cannot be used to define a specific anatomical structure. However, it labels several subsets of T helper cells including CD4+ T cells, T regulatory cells, and T follicular helper cells. This marker is also expressed on red pulp macrophages. This marker represents a prioritized target in the spleen OMAP.

Defines red pulp based on the labeling of splenic endothelial cells. This marker may also be used to define littoral cells in combination with CD8a, cell morphology, and location. This marker represents a core marker and prioritized target in the spleen OMAP.
Defines dark zone germinal center (if present). This marker is essential for assessing cell division and proliferation. This marker represents a prioritized target for the spleen OMAP.
Defines periarteriolar lymphoid sheaths (PALS) and is an essential marker of T cells. This marker represents a core marker and prioritized target in the spleen OMAP.
Defines cytotoxic T cells in the PALS and potentially also littoral cells (in combination with CD31). This marker represents a prioritized target in the spleen OMAP.

Targets a secreted extracellular matrix-associated protein involved in a number of biological processes including tissue remodeling and fibrosis. Protein is present on several distinct lineages including fibroblasts, capillary endothelial cells, platelets, and macrophages.

This marker cannot be used to define a specific anatomical structure. It is used to detect the activation status of many immune cell subsets and labels macrophages, endothelial cells, and fibroblasts in the red pulp. This marker represents a prioritized target in the spleen OMAP.
This marker labels platelets enriched in the red pulp. This marker represents a prioritized target in the spleen OMAP.
Defines the white pulp and is expressed by all hematopoietic cells. This marker represents a prioritized target in the spleen OMAP and can be used for downstream image analysis.

Defines border between red and white pulp. This is an essential marker for many cell types including smooth muscle cells and many subsets of fibroblasts. This marker represents a core marker and prioritized target in the spleen OMAP.
Defines capsule, extracellular matrix components, and central arteries of the spleen. This marker is not a prioritized target in the spleen OMAP.
